# Acceptance Criteria Standard

Every issue and prompt must include acceptance criteria that clearly prove it is complete. Acceptance criteria define the observable conditions that must be true for the work to be considered done.

Acceptance criteria must be:
- Specific
- Testable
- Observable
- Relevant to the issue scope
- Written in plain language
- Focused on outcomes rather than implementation steps
- Include a documentation-update criterion if the change affects any documented behavior (per [core.mdc](core.mdc))

Acceptance criteria should:
- Cover the main success path
- Cover relevant error handling
- Cover important edge cases when applicable
- Include non-functional requirements only when relevant (performance, security, accessibility, logging, auditability)

Acceptance criteria must **not** be:
- Vague
- Process-oriented
- Implementation instructions
- Definitions of Done such as "code reviewed" or "tests added"

---

# Core Rule

Every issue and every prompt must include an `## Acceptance Criteria` section.

That section must contain criteria that allow a reviewer, tester, or stakeholder to determine completion with a clear pass/fail result.

If the criteria do not make completion objectively verifiable, the issue or prompt is **not ready for implementation or review**.

---

# Category-Binding Gate (HARD REQUIREMENT)

If an issue touches a domain covered by a known bug category in [`docs/standards/ISSUE_LOG.md`](../../docs/standards/ISSUE_LOG.md), its acceptance criteria **MUST** include the matching prevention checklist from the relevant `.mdc` rule file. This is not optional — an issue that maps to a CAT but omits the checklist is **defective and not ready for implementation**.

| If the issue touches... | Include checklist from... |
|---|---|
| Frontend build / CSS / styling | [frontend.mdc](frontend.mdc) § CSS Sanity + § Frontend Dockerfile |
| Playwright / browser testing | [frontend.mdc](frontend.mdc) § Playwright Containerization + § Selector Stability |
| Magic Patterns UI | [frontend.mdc](frontend.mdc) § Magic Patterns |
| API response shape / new field | [backend.mdc](backend.mdc) § API Contract Change Checklist |
| Deploy / Dockerfile / compose / CI/CD | [devops.mdc](devops.mdc) § Deployment Permission Gate + § Post-deploy API Contract Verification |
| Terraform / gcloud / infrastructure | [devops.mdc](devops.mdc) § Terraform Safety |
| Database migration | [backend.mdc](backend.mdc) § Database Migrations |

**How to apply**: Copy the relevant checklist items into the issue's `## Acceptance Criteria` section as explicit pass/fail criteria. Do not just reference the rule — **inline** the checks so the implementing agent cannot skip them.

**On issue close**: Update [`docs/standards/ISSUE_LOG.md`](../../docs/standards/ISSUE_LOG.md) with the issue row and `Prevention Added` column if the bug matches an existing category. See [core.mdc](core.mdc) § Issue Log.

---

# Mandatory Frontend Visual AC

**Any issue or prompt that touches `ui-frontend/` MUST include, verbatim, this acceptance criterion:**

> - [ ] UI is visually styled (not raw text). Verified via Playwright screenshot AND CSS sanity assertion (`document.styleSheets[0].cssRules.length > 50` or built CSS bundle >5 KB).

"No JS errors" alone is **not sufficient** — an unstyled app has zero JS errors. See [frontend.mdc](frontend.mdc) § CSS Sanity.

